 hell, the damage doer can be 5 zones away as long as the mobs hate list hasn't reset<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Zoning pulls you off hate list. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
True....but other people who make a mob's hate list can get summoned by a damaged mob, even if the person who actually did the damage is not in the zone any more. Note I said the damage doer can be 5 zones away and the mob will still summon....never said it would summon the person who did damage, just that it will summon people on its hate list, even if they have done no damage to the mob.<br>
<br>
Just to make sure I get no more comments from people who think I don't know what I'm talking about, I'll make it clear what I mean:<br>
<br>
Drood the druid starts killing a deep cavern lotus...starts off with a winged death and drops a moonfire on him for good measure...BOOM...summoned and summarily munched to death. Taynk the warrior who was standing nearby to watch the druid get killed, then gets agroed and nuked by the lotus and starts running for the zone-he was just passing through FG on his way to Twilight, anyway. Now...he's not taunted, snared, cast, hit, smacked, kicked, slammed, or bitchslapped the lotus. But Mr Lotus is hurt and he's pissed...BOOM...Taynk gets summoned and munched.<br>
<br>
<br>
And I forget who said something about Rampage (Narv, I believe)....Rampage is *not* hate...the lists are maintained seperately and the Rampage list is actually maintained in a manner in which the order in which you got placed on the list doesn't change until such time as the mob has lost agro long enough to reset the list....the best guess I've seen of that time frame is 10 minutes, noone but VI knows for sure.<br>
<br>
Or, to clarify, hate lists are dynamic and rampage lists are dynamic.<br>
<br>
<br>
Want proof of all of that? Well, alot of it is from personal observation in 18+ months of playing, and for the rest spend some time reading some of the discussions on boards like Safehouse, Triton, FoH, AL.....if you can work around the flames, there is some good stuff there...<br>
<br>
And Adaster...yes.....I have a massive clue what I'm talking about because I actually take the time to use my brain and think about things I take the time to use my eyes to observe. Try testing the stuff I've said....you'd be amazed how well it works.<br>
<br>
*EDIT* Don't think yer a n00b Morb....just think I wasn't 100% clear in what I said. <p><table border=1>
